article.description: Chris Ferguson threw for five touchdowns and Josh Mack rushed for 248 yards and another score as Maine dominated the final two quarters to beat Rhode Island 51-27 on Saturday in the 96th meeting between the teams.
article.headline: Ferguson throws for 5 TDs, Maine beats Rhode Island 51-27
article.linkText: Ferguson throws for 5 TDs, Maine beats Rhode Island 51-27
article.story: ORONO, Maine -- Chris Ferguson threw for five touchdowns and Josh Mack rushed for 248 yards and another score as Maine dominated the final two quarters to beat Rhode Island 51-27 on Saturday in the 96th meeting between the teams. The Black Bears (2-3, 1-3, Colonial Athletic Association) have now won 11 straight over Rhode Island (1-5, 0-3). Micah Wright returned a punt 77 yards for a score late in the first half to give the Bears their first lead, taking a 23-21 advantage into the break. Mack, who rushed for 185 yards in the second half, ran for one score and Ferguson, a freshman, passed for three more in the third quarter as Maine charged ahead 51-21 going into the fourth. Jaleel Reed caught five passes for 123 yards and three touchdowns. Rhode Island's Aaron Parker caught four passes for 95 yards and one score. -- More AP college football: http://www.collegefootball.ap.org and http://www.twitter.com/AP-Top25
